\par Call Lightning
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Electricity]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Drd 3
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 round
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range: }{\fs20\cf0 Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Effect:}{\fs20\cf0  One or more 30-ft.-long vertical lines of lightning
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 min./level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  Reflex half
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par Immediately upon completion of the spell, and once per round thereafter, you may call down a 5-foot-wide, 30-foot-long, vertical bol
t of lightning that deals 3d6 points of electricity damage. The bolt of lightning flashes down in a vertical stroke at whatever target point you choose within the spell\rquote 
s range (measured from your position at the time). Any creature in the target square or in the path of the bolt is affected.
\par You need not call a bolt of lightning immediately; other actions, even spellcasting, can be performed. However, each round after the first you may use a standard action (concentrating on the spell) to call a bolt. You 
may call a total number of bolts equal to your caster level (maximum 10 bolts).
\par If you are outdoors and in a stormy area\emdash a rain shower, clouds and wind, hot and cloudy conditions, or even a tornado (including a whirlwind formed by a djinni or an air elemental of at least Large size)\emdash 
each bolt deals 3d10 points of electricity damage instead of 3d6.
\par This spell functions indoors or underground but not underwater.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Call Lightning Storm
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Electricity]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Drd 5
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Long (400 ft. + 40 ft./level)
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 call lightning}{\fs20\cf0 , except that each bolt deals 5d6 points of electricity damage (or 5d10 if created outdoors in a stormy area), and you may call a maximum of 15 bolts.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Calm Animals
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Enchantment (Compulsion) [Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Animal 1, Drd 1, Rgr 1
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Targets:}{\fs20\cf0  Animals within 30 ft. of each other
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 min./level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par This spell soothes and
 quiets animals, rendering them docile and harmless. Only ordinary animals (those with Intelligence scores of 1 or 2) can be affected by this spell. All the subjects must be of the same kind, and no two may be more than 30 feet apart. The maximum number o
f Hit Dice of animals you can affect is equal to 2d4 + caster level. A dire animal or an animal trained to attack or guard is allowed a saving throw; other animals are not.
\par The affected creatures remain where they are and do not attack or flee. They are not helpless and defend themselves normally if attacked. Any threat breaks the spell on the threatened creatures.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Calm Emotions
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Enchantment (Compulsion) [Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 2, Clr 2, Law 2
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, DF
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range: }{\fs20\cf0 Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  Creatures in a 20-ft.-radius spread
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Concentration, up to 1 round/level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par This spell calms agitated creatures. You have no control over the affected creatures, but }{\i\fs20\cf0 calm emotions }{\fs20\cf0 
can stop raging creatures from fighting or joyous ones from reveling. Creatures so affected cannot take violent actions (although they can defend themselves) or do anything destructive. Any aggressive action against or damage dealt to a
 calmed creature immediately breaks the spell on all calmed creatures.
\par This spell automatically suppresses (but does not dispel) any morale bonuses granted by spells such as }{\i\fs20\cf0 bless, good hope, }{\fs20\cf0 and }{\i\fs20\cf0 rage, }{\fs20\cf0 as well as negating a bard\rquote s ability to inspire courag
e or a barbarian\rquote s rage ability. It also suppresses any fear effects and removes the }{\i\fs20\cf0 confused }{\fs20\cf0 condition from all targets}{\i\fs20\cf0 . }{\fs20\cf0 
While the spell lasts, a suppressed spell or effect has no effect. When the }{\i\fs20\cf0 calm emotions }{\fs20\cf0 spell ends, the original spell or effect takes hold of the creature again, provided that its duration has not expired in the meantime.

\par 
\par }{\cf0 Cat\rquote s Grace
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Transmutation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 2, Drd 2, Rgr 2, Sor/Wiz 2
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Creature touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 min./level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates (harmless)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par The transmuted creature becomes more graceful, agile, and coordinated. The spell grants a +4 enhancement bonus to Dexterity, adding the usual benefits to AC, Reflex saves, and other uses of the Dexterity modifier.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A pinch of cat fur.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Cat\rquote s Grace, Mass
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Transmutation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 6, Drd 6, Sor/Wiz 6
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Targets:}{\fs20\cf0  One creature/level, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 cat\rquote s grace}{\fs20\cf0 , except that it affects multiple creatures.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Cause Fear
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Necromancy [Fear, Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 1, Clr 1, Death 1, Sor/Wiz 1
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  One living creature with 5 or fewer HD
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1d4 rounds or 1 round; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will partial
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par The affected creature becomes frightened. If the subject succeeds on a Will save, it is shaken for 1 round. Creatures with 6 or more Hit Dice are immune to this effect.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Cause fear }{\fs20\cf0 counters and dispels }{\i\fs20\cf0 remove fear}{\fs20\cf0 .
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Chain Lightning
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Electricity]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Air 6, Sor/Wiz 6
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, F
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Long (400 ft. + 40 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Targets:}{\fs20\cf0  One primary target, plus one secondary target/level (each of which must be within 30 ft. of the primary target)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  Reflex half
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par This spell creates an electrical discharge that begins as a single stroke commencing from your fingertips. Unlike }{\i\fs20\cf0 lightning bolt}{\fs20\cf0 , }{\i\fs20\cf0 chain lightning }{\fs20\cf0 
strikes one object or creature initially, then arcs to other targets.
\par The bolt deals 1d6 points of electricity damage per caster level (maximum 20d6) to the primary target. After it strikes, lightning can arc to a number of secondary targets equal to your caster level (maximum 20). The secondary bolts each strike one target
 and deal half as much damage as the primary one did (rounded down).
\par Each target can attempt a Reflex saving throw for half damage. You choose secondary targets as you like, but they must all be within 30 feet of the primary target, and no target can be str
uck more than once. You can choose to affect fewer secondary targets than the maximum.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Focus: }{\fs20\cf0 A bit of fur; a piece of amber, glass, or a crystal rod; plus one silver pin for each of your caster levels.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Changestaff
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Transmutation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Drd 7
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, F
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 round
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Your touched staff
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 hour/level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par You change a specially prepared quarterstaff into a Huge treantlike creature, about 24 feet tall. When you plant the end
 of the staff in the ground and speak a special command to conclude the casting of the spell, your staff turns into a creature that looks and fights just like a treant. The staff-treant defends you and obeys any spoken commands. However, it is by no means
 
a true treant; it cannot converse with actual treants or control trees. If the staff-treant is reduced to 0 or fewer hit points, it crumbles to powder and the staff is destroyed. Otherwise, the staff returns to its normal form when the spell duration expi
res (or when the spell is dismissed), and it can be used as the focus for another casting of the spell. The staff-treant is always at full strength when created, despite any wounds it may have incurred the last time it appeared.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Focus: }{\fs20\cf0 The quarterstaff, which must be specially prepared. The staff must be a sound limb cut from an ash, oak, or yew, then cured, shaped, carved, and polished (a process requiring twenty-eight days).
\par You cannot adventure or engage in other strenuous activity during the shaping and carving of the staff.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Chaos Hammer
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Chaotic]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Chaos 4
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range: }{\fs20\cf0 Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  20-ft.-radius burst
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous (1d6 rounds); see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will partial; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par You unleash chaotic power to smite your enemies. The power takes the form of a multicolored explosion of leaping, ricocheting energy. Only lawful and neutral (not chaotic) creatures are harmed by the spell.
\par The spell deals 1d8 points of damage per two caster levels (maximum 5d8) to lawful creatures (or 1d6 points of damage per caster level, maximum 10d6, to lawful outsiders) and slows them for 1d6 rounds (see the }{\i\fs20\cf0 slow}{\fs20\cf0  spell). 
A successful Will save reduces the damage by half and negates the slow effect.
\par The spell deals only half damage against creatures who are neither lawful nor chaotic, and they are not slowed. Such a creature can reduce the damage by half again (down to one-quarter) with a successful Will save.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Charm Animal
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Enchantment (Charm) [Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Drd 1, Rgr 1
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  One animal
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 charm person}{\fs20\cf0 , except that it affects a creature of the animal type.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Charm Monster
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Enchantment (Charm) [Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 3, Sor/Wiz 4
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  One living creature
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  One day/level
\par This spell functions like }{\i\fs20\cf0 charm person}{\fs20\cf0 , except that the effect is not restricted by creature type or size.
