\par }{\fs20\cf0 Enchantment (Charm) [Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 1, Sor/Wiz 1
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  One humanoid creature
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 hour/level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par This charm makes a humanoid creature regard you as its trusted friend and ally (treat the target\rquote s attitude as friendly).
 If the creature is currently being threatened or attacked by you or your allies, however, it receives a +5 bonus on its saving throw.
\par The spell does not enable you to control the }{\i\fs20\cf0 charmed }{\fs20\cf0 person as if it were an automaton, but it perceives your words and a
ctions in the most favorable way. You can try to give the subject orders, but you must win an opposed Charisma check to convince it to do anything it wouldn\rquote 
t ordinarily do. (Retries are not allowed.) An affected creature never obeys suicidal or obviously harmful orders, but it might be convinced that something very dangerous is worth doing.  Any act by you or your apparent allies that threatens the }{
\i\fs20\cf0 charmed }{\fs20\cf0 person breaks the spell. You must speak the person\rquote s language to communicate your commands, or else be good at pantomiming.
\par 
